    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.14.39-42_0001"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">217 Neihardt Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">39</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">VICTORIA 
                    3297.
                
                    79A ELIZABETH STREET.
                    S.W.1.</hi>
                </fw>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        London
                        Oct 30/<hi rend="underline">29</hi>
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt Esq</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr Neihardt.</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I returned from the Seville Exhibition last night + found your great epic of the Sioux + Crazy Horse, waiting for me.</p>
                
                <p>I have been taking a look at it. What a <unclear>subject</unclear>!
                
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.14.39-42_0002"/>
                    <fw type="curatorial">40</fw>
                    <fw type="authorial"><hi rend="underline">2</hi></fw>
                    
                    Certainly you handle it with knowledge and sympathy.</p>
                
                <p>It ought to have been written, + it was fitting that the grandson of a pioneer should write it.</p>
                
                <p>The <unclear>illustrations</unclear> with the "Pinto", + the "<unclear>bocado</unclear>" in his mouth is very <unclear>spirited</unclear> and brings back many memories.</p>
                
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.14.39-42_0003"/>
                    <fw type="curatorial">41</fw>
                    <fw type="authorial"><hi rend="underline">3.</hi></fw>
                
                <p>Do you know "Long Lance"? I wrote him, to the <unclear>Blood</unclear> Indian Reservation on the appearance of his fine book, but got no answer.</p>
                
                <p>Plenty bad Indian! Again <unclear/> you or <unclear/> myself &#8212; <unclear>great</unclear> interest + pleasure from
                
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.14.39-42_0004"/>
                    <fw type="curatorial">42</fw>
                    <fw type="authorial"><hi rend="underline">4.</hi></fw>
                
                    a detailed reading of your Epic.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours sincerely</salute>
                    
                    <signed>R.B. Cunningham Graham</signed>
                    <note type="curatorial"><hi rend="caps">R.B.</hi> Cunningham Graham</note>
                </closer>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Found in <hi rend="underline">Thirty Tales and Sketches</hi> <hi rend="caps">R.B.C.</hi> <del/><add>G</add>raham The Viking Press <hi rend="caps">NY</hi> 1929</note>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
